Loe here the pearle, whom God and man doth loue
1 sheet ([1] p.) : port. (woodcut).
G. Godet, [London : 1563]
Title from first two lines of text. A woodcut portrait of Queen Elizabeth holding a pearl with verse bellow. Imprint from STC. Entered in Stationer's Register to G. Godhead, 1562-63. Cf. STC. Reproduction of original in the British Library.
